apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 MALAYLAY, Philippines (AP) A strong earthquake rocked the Philippine island of Mindoro early Tuesday, killing at least 23 people many as they slept and destroying nearly 200 homes. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 In Malaylay, a small fishing village on the northern coast of the island, at least 23 people died, eight were missing, and 32 homes were destroyed, officials and police said. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Injured people sitting and crying in the rubble of their homes said that moments after the quake struck a wall of water washed through their devastated village on the mouth of a river. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 DZRH and DZMM radio reported that at least 31 people died on the island, many while sleeping in buildings that collapsed, including a Philippine Coast Guard structure. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Both stations quoted Rodolfo Valencia, one of the island's two governors. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Lourdes Masing, the disaster-service director of the National Red Cross in Manila, said at least six people died, 31 were injured, one was missing, and 188 homes were heavily damaged. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Mindoro Island is still recovering from a typhoon that struck the area last month, destroying much of the coconut and rice that famrs grow in small fields there. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 President Fidel Ramos, who is at the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation Forum in Indonesia, ordered 5 million pesos (dlrs 208,000) sent to the islands to help rebuild destroyed homes. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Food and medical supplies were being rushed to the island on four military helicopters. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 The quake, which occurred at 3:15 am (14:15 Monday GMT), had a preliminary magnitude of 7 and was centered in a strait 10 kilometers (six miles) north of Calapan, a town on the northern end of the island, said the Philippine Institute of Vulcanology and Seismology. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Calapan is less than 5 kilometers (3 miles) east of Malaylay. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Lasting about four minutes, the quake was felt at intensities of 3 and 4 throughout central and south Philippines, including Manila, 75 miles (120 kilometers) north of the epicenter, said Ted Sandoval, a specialist at the institute. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 The U.S. Geological Survey in Menlo Park, Calif., and the Royal Hong Kong Observatory both put the quake's preliminary magnitude at 7.1. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 No damage was immediately reported in Manila, where people in large hotels woke up as they shook, or in other areas outside Mindoro Island, a police spokesman in Manila said. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 Gov. Valencia told radio stations that some homes were washed away by large waves, and three bridges were damaged and closed. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 But Sandoval said no tidal waves were reported or expected from the quake, one of the strongest ever to occur on the Lubang fault, one of the area's most active. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 A magnitude 6 quake can cause severe damage if centered under a populated area, while amgnitude 7 quake indicates a major quake capable of widespread, heavy damage. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 The Philippines, a Pacific archipelago of 7,100 mountainous islands, sits on at least four major faults. 
apwsE9511250054-2-2-1 An earthquake in 1990 killed nearly 2,000 people on the main island of Luzon. 
